admin panel data.jsonDone! Here's what was implemented:

Land Cost Input in Budget Tab:

Added a Land Cost (₹) input field at the top of the Budget tab
Shows the "With Stamp/Legal" amount (+6.5%) next to the input
Auto-saves to project.underwriting.actualLandPurchaseCost (persists across sessions)
ROI/Profit now includes Land Cost:

Project Cost = Construction Cost + Land Cost (with stamp/legal)
Profit = Revenue − (Construction + Land)
ROI = Profit / Total Cost × 100
Both Dashboard and Budget tabs use the same land-cost-inclusive formula
Reports auto-connected:

Both feasibility-report and underwriting-report already read from project.underwriting.actualLandPurchaseCost, so the value you enter in the Budget tab will flow through to both reports automatically.
Run npm run dev to test.
